parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or hesitate to respond, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle loses motive power
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A shift system fault can cause the vehicle to fail to shift into gear, leading to loss of motive power, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The "Shift System Fault" warning light is illuminated
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle fails to move or respond as needed
the shifter cable is detached or worn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A coolant leak can cause engine failure, leading to overheating, engine block cracking, and potentially a fire.
symptoms: The coolant level is low
the temperature gauge fluctuates
the engine misfires
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Torque converter failure can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or hesitate to respond, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle loses motive power
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant intrusion into the engine can cause misfires, engine failure, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: White smoke from the exhaust
check engine light illumination
engine shaking or vibrating
loss of power
hesitation
coolant level dropping
overheating
and misfires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine failure
loss of power
stalling
overheating
and misfires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the battery to drain, resulting in the vehicle being unable to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery keeps dying
the vehicle requires a jumpstart
the dashboard goes black
the engine stops
and the gear shift spins into park making a grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the transmission shifts into park unexpectedly
the vehicle will not shift from park to neutral or drive
and the gear shift makes a grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, making it difficult to stop, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks from underneath the front passenger's side wheel
the vehicle will not immediately start while pressing the brake pedal and START/STOP button
and the brake hand be activated while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbags do not deploy in an accident
and the Restraint Control Module (RCM) fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk and door system can cause the trunk to open unexpectedly while driving, which can lead to accidents or distractions.
symptoms: The trunk keeps popping open on its own while driving
and the trunk opens unexpectedly when not in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the climate control system can cause the air conditioner blower to turn on unexpectedly, which can lead to distractions while driving.
symptoms: The air conditioner blower turns on all by itself while driving
and the on/off button for the radio stops working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the APIM can cause the 12v battery to drain, resulting in the vehicle being unable to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The APIM is malfunctioning
causing a constant drain on the 12v battery system
and the 12v battery keeps dying.
